audit-b14: cmm defensive sweep — strncpy -> strscpy

Mechanical rewrite across 10 cmm/src TUs converting all strncpy()
callsites to strscpy(). cmm is userspace; strscpy is provided by libbsd
(already linked, used by B6/B7/B12).

Coverage (23 sites total):

  module_vlan.c   2 sites
  module_tunnel.c 4 sites
  module_rx.c     7 sites
  module_lro.c    1 site
  module_qm.c     2 sites
  module_relay.c  2 sites
  cmm.c           1 site
  module_stat.c   1 site
  itf.c           2 sites
  voicebuf.c      1 site

All destinations are stack/struct char arrays for interface names or
config tokens. None depend on NUL-padding behaviour.

No behaviour change on the well-formed input path. Truncation now
always NUL-terminates within the dst bound instead of potentially
emitting a non-terminated string.

